Setting up git

https://help.github.com/articles/set-up-git/


Local Repo

1.cd project_folder

2.git init - Initializes Local Repo - .git hidden folder appears

3.git add <filename>,rm --cached files - Add files to staging(git add . to add all files).

4.git status  - Reports files that have changed

5.git commit - Goes to vim editor kind of mode. 
Press I for insert mode and type in commit message. Esc+:wq takes you out. 
In nano use Ctrl+X and Enter.
 
OR

git commit -m "Message" to skip all the vim,nano stages.


6. .gitignore - Folder/Document that contains filenames to be ignored
touch .gitignore - Open it and put all filenames which have to be ignored

7. git branch branchname - To create new branch
   git checkout branchname - To switch branches
   git merge branchname - To megre branch with master
   Make changes in branches and merge finally


Remote Repo-github

1. Create repo in github
2. git remote add origin 'url' - Add remote repo / git remote rm origin -To remove remote
3. git push -u origin master - To push contents from local repo to remote repo
4. git pull origin master - To reflect changes made by others contributors on your local repo.

Cloning

1.Open new folder 
2.git clone 'url'

